cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "SYNAPSE CHANNEL: Local-first multi-agent coordination bus"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Šotek"
    given-names: "Miroslav"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0009-3560-0851"
    affiliation: "ANULUM CH & LI"
version: 0.99.4
date-released: "2026-07-11"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.20801559"
license: "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
repository-code: "https://github.com/anulum/synapse-channel"
url: "https://www.anulum.li"
abstract: >-
  A local-first coordination bus for a fleet of AI agents working in parallel —
  within one repository or across a whole ecosystem of them. A single WebSocket hub
  is the authoritative source of truth for presence, file-scoped work claims, chat,
  a typed task lifecycle, a shared task plan, agent capabilities, and resource
  offers, with crash-durable persistence
  (append-only SQLite WAL with replay), reconnect-safe idempotency, atomic
  handoff, resumable checkpoints, an LLM-free stall supervisor, proportionate
  connect authentication, and task-class routing to tiered backends.
keywords:
  - multi-agent coordination
  - websocket
  - task claims
  - local-first
  - event sourcing
  - blackboard
  - agent orchestration
